      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CHAMPAGNE ROUGE (5) comes here deep into the prep in a fairly average contest. Faded quickly in the straight to run seventh behind Tajawal over 2050m at Gold Coast in BM65 class. Well placed for this and can bounce back quickly. REDADEL (6) massive jump in class and trip with a game on-pace Maiden win over 2220m at this track in C1 company. Will relish Spokes' claim again and can keep the winning momentum going. VERMEER (3) thereabouts of late and doesn't have to improve much to win this. Covered ground from back in the field with a battling fifth over 2180m at Ipswich. Placed to advantage from the inside draw and represents good each way value. HURRICANE ROSIE (4) in a good staying yard and strips fitter for this. Was a month between runs with a fading ninth over 2050m at the Gold Coast. Finds a weaker contest and no shock to see her take a hand in the finish.",
